Water level is 2" above the old high water mark + at least 12" higher than last August (1998).
Two loons swam within 25' of my pontoon boat.  Very content.  Two ospreys are on the nest with their young.
Two ospreys sitting on their nest feeding their young.  Lots of chirpin' + squeakin'.
2 loons were 40' from my pontoon boat and fishing- unconcerned with me- no ospreys on their nest yet.
Ospreys are on their nest-lots of chirpin and squeakin going on-sounds like young ones-also saw a mallard with young ones.
Ospry was feeding 2 young ones high on the nest-mouth to mouth fish- lots of pondweed blooming.
Pondweed is most abudant- chick osprey reported dead under a neighbors pier-given to DNR for a study.
2 loons and 2 ospreys were observed fishing.
Ospreys and loons went South for the winter.
Pondweed is growing in epic proportions- very abundant.
Large pondweed is horrible and covers more than half the lake! DNR will check it out 8-20-02.
70% of large pondweed was removed last week by mechanical harvesting. Loons and ospreys are still here.
The clearest the lake has ever been.
Partly sunny.  Windy - cold front coming in.
Sunny- 75 F.  Easy summer breeze.  Awesome day.
Water Level very low for this time of year
A beautiful autumn day- sunny- slight breeze- 48F
Mostly cloudy with some spotty sun- air temperature 46 degrees.
Sunny- 74 degrees. Water is cloudy today. Blue/Green algae.
Sunny Fall day. Air temperature 42 degrees.
Warm sunny day - Air temperature is 88 degrees. Already seeing some blue/green algae blooms.
Partly Sunny- air temperature is 79 degrees.
Warm sunny day - Air temperature is 88 degrees. Already seeing some blue/green algae blooms.
78 degrees and Sunny - Algae bloom is already very apparent. 78 degrees and Sunny - Algae bloom is already very apparent.
Partly sunny w/air temperature of 39 degrees
Party Cloudy- humid- air temperature 82 degrees.

column1: Had company today on the lake. My son Matt helped me.
I saw the first couple of blue/green algae blooms while I was testing. Both were reasonably small compared to what I've seen this time a year ago. Hopefully that is a positive sign..

column2: It's a nice sunny day. Air temperature is 76 degrees.

column1: I see small pockets of the blue/green algae- but nothing significant.

column2: Sunny and very windy. The boats moving around pretty good today! 56 degrees.

column1: The water looks brown and pretty good.
